Sentencas: Electrolyte-supported solid oxide fuel cells (NiO-1Ce10ScZr vertical bar 1Ce10ScZr vertical bar LSM-1Ce10ScZr) were prepared in this study.
Titulo: Improving the electrochemical properties of SSZ electrolyte-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The effects of cosintering temperatures of cathode and anode with electrolyte and the additions of metal oxide (Bi2O3 and CeO2) in the anode on the microstructures and electrochemical properties were investigated.
Titulo: Improving the electrochemical properties of SSZ electrolyte-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The carbon deposition behaviors of the anode with added CeO2 were also evaluated.
Titulo: Improving the electrochemical properties of SSZ electrolyte-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Results indicated that the maximum power density (P-max) initially increased from 0.28 W/cm(2) (1150 degrees C) to 0.35 W/cm(2) (1250 degrees C), and then decreased to 0.33 W/cm(2) (1300 degrees C) with the increase in co-sintering temperature from 1150 degrees C to 1300 degrees C.
Titulo: Improving the electrochemical properties of SSZ electrolyte-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The variation tendency of P-max was attributed to a complex combination of the bond strength increase of the interfaces and the densification of the electrodes with the increase of the co-sintering temperature.
Titulo: Improving the electrochemical properties of SSZ electrolyte-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Adding proper CeO2 in the anode effectively improved the electrochemical properties of the ZrO2 doped with Sc2O3 electrolyte-supported single cells.
Titulo: Improving the electrochemical properties of SSZ electrolyte-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This phenomenon could be related to the increase of the dimension of three-phase boundary.
Titulo: Improving the electrochemical properties of SSZ electrolyte-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The P-max of the SSZ electrolyte-supported single cell with the anode mixed with 1.0 wt% CeO2 could reach 0.42 W/cm(2).
Titulo: Improving the electrochemical properties of SSZ electrolyte-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The mixture of 1.0 wt% CeO2 in the anode could also effectively suppress the carbon deposition of CH4 on the anode surface.
Titulo: Improving the electrochemical properties of SSZ electrolyte-supported solid oxide fuel cells
